        <section id="collaborations" class="glass-card p-6 space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-accent">COLLABORATIONS &amp; FEATURES</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-text/90 prose-p:mb-6 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
            <h3>International Collaborations</h3>
            <p><strong>Concrete Noir - "Romance Ruins" (November 2025)</strong></p>

            <p>Viktória Šmídová provided vocals for "Faraway Places," track 10 on this debut LP by Italian darkwave artist Piero Fragola, released via Frequens Records on November 3, 2025. The album, created entirely with modular synthesizers on Tiptop Audio's ART system, explores themes of romanticism as destruction and rebirth through eleven tracks of introspective electronic music. This collaboration represents Lishkee's first feature on a major international label release, connecting the Czech indie scene with the European darkwave and coldwave underground.</p>

            <p><em>About Concrete Noir:</em> Piero Fragola is a Florence-based multimedia artist and sound designer known for his genre-defying projects including We Love (BPitch Control/Ellen Allien) and ANGLE (Tiptop Audio Records). His work as Concrete Noir explores a hybrid space where electronics, voice, and imagery merge into an introspective and shadowy form, combining wave, darkwave, and synth-pop with modular synthesis.</p>

            <h4 class="mt-4">Luca Minelli Collaborations</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>"Endlessly" (November 2024)</li>
              <li>"Silver (Modular Version)" (May 2025) - featuring experimental modular synthesis recorded in a single take</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="mt-4">Theater &amp; Multimedia Projects</h3>
            <p><strong>Labyrint (2024-2025)</strong></p>
            <p><strong>Site-Specific Theater Performance | Káznice, Brno</strong></p>

            <p>Lishkee provided original music for this immersive theatrical experience at the former Brno prison (Káznice), one of the city's most historically significant and atmospheric cultural spaces. The performance, described as an "imaginative collage," guides audiences through the historic building while blending theatrical and audiovisual elements.</p>

            <p><strong>Production Details:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Collaboration with Divadelní smečka (theater collective based at Káznice)</li>
              <li>Dancers and performers from Brno</li>
              <li>Filmmaker Petr Kačírka</li>
              <li>Directors: Pavel Strašák and Zdeňka Kučerová</li>
            </ul>

            <p>The production reflects on the contemporary revival of this unique brownfield site while incorporating historical references to the late Baroque period (when Káznice was built) and the 1950s Communist terror era. Lishkee's atmospheric electronic compositions provided the sonic landscape for this exploration of history, memory, and transformation.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="press-media" class="glass-card p-6 space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-accent">PRESS &amp; MEDIA</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-text/90 prose-p:mb-6 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
            <h3>Featured In</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Full Moon Magazine (FMZine)</strong> - Czech Republic's leading independent music magazine covering both local and international music scenes, as well as film, comics, and design since 2010. Winner of Press of the Year at Nouvelle Prague festival (2018, 2019).</li>
              <li><strong>electronica.org.uk / Frequency State</strong> - UK-based electronic music publication</li>
              <li><strong>Radio_FM</strong> (Slovakia) - Alternative music radio station</li>
              <li><strong>Pohoda Festival</strong> (Slovakia) - Featured artist announcement and profile</li>
              <li><strong>Bandzone.cz</strong> - Czech music community platform</li>
              <li><strong>Melodka Club</strong> - Brno venue featured artist profiles</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Press Reviews &amp; Recognition</h4>
            <p><strong>On "Silver (Modular Version)" ft. Luca Minelli:</strong></p>
            <blockquote>"An engaging blend of dreamy synth textures and delicate vocals... The modular synths, recorded in one take, lend the track a sense of spontaneity and organic movement... maintains a delicate balance between experimental sound design and a clear, melodic core. Lishkee's music is known for its blend of indie-pop, lo-fi, indietronica, and downtempo styles. Their sound often carries a cozy, nostalgic feel, with lyrics that explore personal themes like anxiety and self-reflection." — Frequency State / electronica.org.uk (May 2025)</blockquote>

            <p><strong>On Live Performance with Whyohwhy (Alterna, Brno):</strong></p>
            <blockquote>"Lishkee otvárali s charakteristickým spojením elektronických beatov, snových gitár a jazzovo ladeného vokálu." [Lishkee opened with their characteristic combination of electronic beats, dreamy guitars and jazz-inflected vocals.] — FMZine (February 2025)</blockquote>

            <p><strong>On Stereofox (FMZine "10+1" Feature):</strong></p>
            <blockquote>"Česko-slovenské duo producenta Radima Kocourka a zpěvačky a instrumentalistky Viktórie Šmídové kombinuje psychedelii, trip hop, dream pop i experimentální prvky. Ozkoušeno na Pohodě nebo na Radiu Wave, kde se singl Distortion umístil na stříbrné příčce v soutěži začínajících skupin Startér." [Czech-Slovak duo of producer Radim Kocourek and singer/instrumentalist Viktória Šmídová combines psychedelia, trip hop, dream pop and experimental elements. Tested at Pohoda and on Radio Wave, where the single "Distortion" placed second in the Startér competition for emerging groups.] — FMZine (2018)</blockquote>

            <p><strong>Pohoda Festival Artist Announcement (as Stereofox):</strong></p>
            <blockquote>"Na Pohode zahrá aj elektronicko-gitarové duo Stereofox. Ich tvorba kombinuje psychedéliu a dream pop s experimentálnymi prvkami... Minulý rok vydali na Bandcampe demo album Layers, ktorý sa dostal na longlist Radio_Head Awards 2017 v kategórii debut roka." [At Pohoda will also play electronic-guitar duo Stereofox. Their work combines psychedelia and dream pop with experimental elements... Last year they released demo album Layers on Bandcamp, which made the longlist of Radio_Head Awards 2017 in the debut of the year category.] — Pohoda Festival (2018)</blockquote>

            <p><strong>Bandzone.cz User Review:</strong></p>
            <blockquote>"Máte na to stát se českými (moravskými) Massive Attack!!! Přejeme hodně nápadů v další tvorbě. Jste jedna z mála kapel tady, co je trochu originální." [You have what it takes to become the Czech (Moravian) Massive Attack!!! We wish you many ideas in future work. You are one of the few bands here that is somewhat original.] — Bandzone.cz</blockquote>

            <h4>Awards &amp; Nominations</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Radio_Head Awards</strong> - Debut of the Year Nomination (longlist) for "<a href="https://lishkee.bandcamp.com/album/layers-2?t=2" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Layers" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover underline underline-offset-2 transition-colors">𝓛𝓪𝔂𝓮𝓻𝓼</a>" album (Slovakia, 2017, as Stereofox)</li>
              <li><strong>Radio Wave Startér</strong> - Second Place (Silver) with "<a href="https://lishkee.bandcamp.com/track/distortions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Distortions" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover underline underline-offset-2 transition-colors">𝓓𝓲𝓼𝓽𝓸𝓻𝓽𝓲𝓸𝓷𝓼</a>" (Czech Republic, 2018), leading to performance at Pohoda Festival</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="band-members" class="glass-card p-6 space-y-4">
